<paragraph id="8B9536BBFFB5DF25B3B17D94FD5BF8D4" blockId="25.[191,1440,1727,1922]" pageId="25" pageNumber="24">
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D38FFB5DF25B3B17D94FE56F932" authorityName="Meyrick" authorityYear="1913" baseAuthorityName="Brown &amp; Razowski &amp; Aarvik &amp; Timm &amp; Copeland" baseAuthorityYear="1913" box="[192,388,1727,1753]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Eucosma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="salticola">
<emphasis id="B95EEAA9FFB5DF25B3B17D94FE56F932" box="[192,388,1727,1753]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="24">Eucosma salticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from 
<specimenCount id="9D2CFD32FFB5DF25B1047DEBFCC2F932" box="[629,784,1727,1753]" pageId="25" pageNumber="24" type="generic">12 specimens</specimenCount>
, including both sexes, from Barberton, Three Sisters, and Waterval Onder, Transvaal, 
<collectingCountry id="F33D762BFFB5DF25B28E7DB5FD41F910" box="[511,659,1761,1787]" name="South Africa" pageId="25" pageNumber="24">South Africa</collectingCountry>
. According to 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBB4B4AFFB5DF25B04F7DB5FB5AF910" author="Razowski J &amp; Kruger M." box="[830,1160,1761,1787]" pageId="25" pageNumber="24" pagination="103 - 179" refId="ref18553" refString="Razowski J, Kruger M. 2007. An illustrated catalogue of the type specimens of Tortricidae in the Transvaal Museum, Pretoria (Lepidoptera: Tortricidae). SHILAP Revista de Lepidopterologia 35: 103 - 179." type="journal article" year="2007">Razowski and Krüger (2007)</bibRefCitation>
, in addition to the male 
<typeStatus id="54918819FFB5DF25B3B17C56FEF6F8F7" box="[192,292,1794,1820]" pageId="25" pageNumber="24">holotype</typeStatus>
, there are 
<specimenCount id="9D2CFD32FFB5DF25B2E57C56FDFFF8F6" box="[404,557,1794,1821]" pageId="25" pageNumber="24" type="generic" typeStatus="paratypes">five paratypes</specimenCount>
in the DMP. The female 
<typeStatus id="54918819FFB5DF25B04A7C56FC4FF8F7" box="[827,925,1794,1820]" pageId="25" pageNumber="24">holotype</typeStatus>
and its genitalia were figured by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBB4B4AFFB5DF25B6777C56FE8BF8D5" author="Razowski J &amp; Kruger M." pageId="25" pageNumber="24" pagination="103 - 179" refId="ref18553" refString="Razowski J, Kruger M. 2007. An illustrated catalogue of the type specimens of Tortricidae in the Transvaal Museum, Pretoria (Lepidoptera: Tortricidae). SHILAP Revista de Lepidopterologia 35: 103 - 179." type="journal article" year="2007">Razowski and Krüger (2007</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 147, 310, respectively).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9536BBFFB5DF26B2717C12FECDFEF9" blockId="25.[191,1440,1727,1922]" lastBlockId="26.[191,1441,214,475]" lastPageId="26" lastPageNumber="25" pageId="25" pageNumber="24">
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D38FFB5DF25B2717C12FE3CF88B" authorityName="Razowski and Wojtusiak" authorityYear="2012" box="[256,494,1862,1888]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Eucosmocydia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="prolixa">
<emphasis id="B95EEAA9FFB5DF25B2717C12FE3CF88B" box="[256,494,1862,1888]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="24">Eucosmocydia prolixa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from a 
<typeStatus id="54918819FFB5DF25B1937C12FC96F88B" box="[738,836,1862,1888]" pageId="25" pageNumber="24">holotype</typeStatus>
male from the Obudu 
<collectingRegion id="49EEF859FFB5DF25B74F7C12FB40F88B" box="[1086,1170,1862,1888]" country="Nigeria" name="Plateau" pageId="25" pageNumber="24">Plateau</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F33D762BFFB5DF25B7EB7C12FB3DF88B" box="[1178,1263,1862,1888]" name="Nigeria" pageId="25" pageNumber="24">Nigeria</collectingCountry>
; the description was accompanied by illustrations of the adult and genitalia (
<bibRefCitation id="EFBB4B4AFFB5DF25B0177C33FB6CF86A" author="Razowski J &amp; Wojtusiak J." box="[870,1214,1895,1921]" pageId="25" pageNumber="24" pagination="59 - 130" refId="ref18616" refString="Razowski J, Wojtusiak J. 2012. Tortricidae (Lepidoptera) from Nigeria. Acta Zoologica Cracoviensia 55 (2): 59 - 130." type="journal article" year="2012">Razowski and Wojtusiak 2012</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 36, 131). Based on forewing maculation and morphology of the male genitalia, 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D38FFB6DF26B0F87B83FC21FF1B" authorityName="Razowski and Wojtusiak" authorityYear="2012" box="[905,1011,214,240]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Eucosmocydia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="prolixa">
<emphasis id="B95EEAA9FFB6DF26B0F87B83FC21FF1B" box="[905,1011,214,240]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">E. prolixa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is almost certainly conspecific with 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D38FFB6DF26B6FB7B83FECBFEFA" authorityName="Meyrick" authorityYear="1913" baseAuthorityName="Brown &amp; Razowski &amp; Aarvik &amp; Timm &amp; Copeland" baseAuthorityYear="1913" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Eucosma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="salticola">
<emphasis id="B95EEAA9FFB6DF26B6FB7B83FECBFEFA" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">E. salticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3306530FFB6DF26B2717A4DFD26FE30" pageId="26" pageNumber="25" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B9536BBFFB6DF26B2717A4DFD26FE30" blockId="26.[191,1441,214,475]" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">
One of us (LA) has dissected specimens from 
<collectingCountry id="F33D762BFFB6DF26B0777A4DFC4AFED8" box="[774,920,281,307]" name="South Africa" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">South Africa</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F33D762BFFB6DF26B0D27A4DFC2AFED8" box="[931,1016,281,307]" name="Malawi" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">Malawi</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F33D762BFFB6DF26B7727A4DFB99FED8" box="[1027,1099,281,307]" name="Kenya" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">Kenya</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry id="F33D762BFFB6DF26B7F67A4DFB0CFED8" box="[1159,1246,281,307]" name="Uganda" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">Uganda</collectingCountry>
that superficially resemble the 
<typeStatus id="54918819FFB6DF26B2267A6FFE55FEBE" box="[343,391,315,341]" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">type</typeStatus>
specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D38FFB6DF26B16E7A6FFD47FEBF" authorityName="Meyrick" authorityYear="1913" baseAuthorityName="Brown &amp; Razowski &amp; Aarvik &amp; Timm &amp; Copeland" baseAuthorityYear="1913" box="[543,661,314,340]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Eucosma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="salticola">
<emphasis id="B95EEAA9FFB6DF26B16E7A6FFD47FEBF" box="[543,661,314,340]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">E. salticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
figured by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBB4B4AFFB6DF26B0647A6EFB80FEBE" author="Razowski J &amp; Kruger M." box="[789,1106,314,341]" pageId="26" pageNumber="25" pagination="103 - 179" refId="ref18553" refString="Razowski J, Kruger M. 2007. An illustrated catalogue of the type specimens of Tortricidae in the Transvaal Museum, Pretoria (Lepidoptera: Tortricidae). SHILAP Revista de Lepidopterologia 35: 103 - 179." type="journal article" year="2007">Razowski and Krüger (2007</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 147), and the genitalia of those specimens are nearly indistinguishable from those illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBB4B4AFFB6DF26B0A67A08FAC2FE9D" author="Razowski J &amp; Kruger M." box="[983,1296,348,375]" pageId="26" pageNumber="25" pagination="103 - 179" refId="ref18553" refString="Razowski J, Kruger M. 2007. An illustrated catalogue of the type specimens of Tortricidae in the Transvaal Museum, Pretoria (Lepidoptera: Tortricidae). SHILAP Revista de Lepidopterologia 35: 103 - 179." type="journal article" year="2007">Razowski and Krüger (2007</bibRefCitation>
, female) and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBB4B4AFFB6DF26B3B07A2AFDC8FE73" author="Razowski J &amp; Wojtusiak J." box="[193,538,382,408]" pageId="26" pageNumber="25" pagination="59 - 130" refId="ref18616" refString="Razowski J, Wojtusiak J. 2012. Tortricidae (Lepidoptera) from Nigeria. Acta Zoologica Cracoviensia 55 (2): 59 - 130." type="journal article" year="2012">Razowski and Wojtusiak (2012</bibRefCitation>
, male). Although the adult of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D38FFB6DF26B0147A2BFC1DFE73" authorityName="Razowski and Wojtusiak" authorityYear="2012" box="[869,975,382,408]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Eucosmocydia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="prolixa">
<emphasis id="B95EEAA9FFB6DF26B0147A2BFC1DFE73" box="[869,975,382,408]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">E. prolixa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a slightly different forewing color, the pattern is essentially the same as that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D38FFB6DF26B1047AF4FD38FE52" authorityName="Meyrick" authorityYear="1913" baseAuthorityName="Brown &amp; Razowski &amp; Aarvik &amp; Timm &amp; Copeland" baseAuthorityYear="1913" box="[629,746,415,441]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Eucosma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="salticola">
<emphasis id="B95EEAA9FFB6DF26B1047AF4FD38FE52" box="[629,746,415,441]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">E. salticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and the female genitalia of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D38FFB6DF26B76E7AF4FB41FE52" authorityName="Meyrick" authorityYear="1913" baseAuthorityName="Brown &amp; Razowski &amp; Aarvik &amp; Timm &amp; Copeland" baseAuthorityYear="1913" box="[1055,1171,415,441]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Eucosma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="salticola">
<emphasis id="B95EEAA9FFB6DF26B76E7AF4FB41FE52" box="[1055,1171,415,441]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">E. salticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
strongly resemble those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D38FFB6DF26B3AC7A96FE94FE30" authorityName="Razowski and Wojtusiak" authorityYear="2012" box="[221,326,449,475]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Eucosmocydia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="prolixa">
<emphasis id="B95EEAA9FFB6DF26B3AC7A96FE94FE30" box="[221,326,449,475]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">E. prolixa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBB4B4AFFB6DF26B20E7A95FD44FE30" author="Agassiz DJL &amp; Aarvik L." box="[383,662,449,475]" pageId="26" pageNumber="25" pagination="369 - 397" refId="ref17150" refString="Agassiz DJL, Aarvik L. 2014. New Tortricidae (Lepidoptera) from East Africa with an account of the tortricid fauna of acacia in the Kenyan Rift Valley. Zootaxa 3861: 369 - 397." type="journal article" year="2014">Agassiz and Aarvik 2014</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 33).
</paragraph>
